                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d75">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/5757: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-01-16T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >January 16, 1933—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 16—6:44 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>54. Liu Chung-chieh, Vice Minister of Foreign Affairs, called. He stated he was
                    in Peiping to maintain liaison between Nanking and Chang Hsueh-liang and to
                    maintain contact with the Legations as Nanking realized Ministers could not go
                    to Nanking at this time. He stated that Suma of the Japanese Legation at
                    Shanghai had called on Wu Tieh-cheng<note n="3" xml:id="d75fn3">Known also as
                        Gen. Wu Te-chen; mayor of Greater Shanghai.</note> to say that Japanese
                    Foreign Office and military <pb facs="0193" n="91" xml:id="pg_91"/> were agreed
                    that nothing should be done to aggravate situation and to express the hope that
                    Chinese would refrain from moving forces in the direction of Shanhaikwan. Liu
                    stated Nanking’s reply was that Japanese had taken initiative at Shanhaikwan
                    thereby aggravating situation. Nanking expressed the hope that Japanese would
                    withdraw from Shanhaikwan voluntarily.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
